body:
Given the following code: <!-- Please provide a link to play.rust-lang.org -->

```rust
use std::{borrow::BorrowMut, cell::RefCell, rc::Rc};

pub struct Foo {
    bar: (),
}

fn foo() {
    let foo = Rc::new(RefCell::new(Foo { bar: () }));
    let bar = foo.borrow_mut().bar;
}
```

[Playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=27c35dea78a72527eff5eaf0c86c0095)

The current output is:

```
error[E0609]: no field `bar` on type `&mut Rc<RefCell<Foo>>`
 --> src/lib.rs:9:32  |
9 |     let bar = foo.borrow_mut().bar;
  |                                ^^^ unknown field
```

Here, `borrow_mut` uses `BorrowMut::borrow_mut` instead of `RefCell::borrow_mut` which can be confusing especially for beginners. Wondering if the diagnostics can/should be improved to help.

`borrow` doesn't have the same problem because it will cause an error, AFAICT because of the conflict between `<&T as Borrow>::borrow` and `<Rc as Borrow>::borrow`.
